Package: vnc
Version: 3.3.3r2
Revision: 5
Source: http://ftp.uk.research.att.com/pub/vnc/dist/vnc-%v_unixsrc.tgz
BuildDepends: dlcompat-dev
Depends: x11
SourceDirectory: vnc_unixsrc
PatchScript:  sed 's|<PREFIX>|%p|g' < %a/%f.patch | patch -p1
CompileScript: <<
 xmkmf
 make World CC=cc LOCAL_LDFLAGS="-force_flat_namespace"
 ( cd ./Xvnc; make World)
<<
InstallScript: <<
 mkdir -p %i/bin
 mkdir -p %i/share/vnc/classes
 ./vncinstall %i/bin
 cp ./classes/* %i/share/vnc/classes
<<
Description: Remote display system for X11
DescDetail: creates a virtual X11 windowing environment that can be viewed
  not only on the machine where it is running, but from anywhere on the Internet
  and from a wide variety of machine architectures.
DescPort: Installs plain vanilla vnc. For enhanced version, use tightvnc.
 Uses Imake. 
 Requires XFree86 development stuff (Xprog.tgz), and perl.
 Assumes XFree86 installed in /usr/X11R6.
 The "-localhost" and "-inetd" options for Xvnc are broken on MacOS X/Darwin.
 Includes mini http server and java applet for remote access via a web browser.
DescUsage: User must add /usr/X11R6/bin to PATH in order to run vncserver.
 XAUTHORITY environment variable must be set to ${HOME}/.vnc/.Xauthority in
 xstartup file.
 Detailed usage instructions at http://www.uk.research.att.com/vnc.
License: GPL
Conflicts: tightvnc
Replaces: tightvnc
DocFiles: LICENCE.TXT README 
